Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. JOHANNESBURG - Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma has extended the National State of Disaster by a month. Lockdown will now continue until 15 November 2020. The extension, Dlamini-Zuma says, allows the government to put plans in place to prevent a second wave of COVID-19 infections. According to the Department of Health, SA's COVID-19 deathÂ toll is at 18,028.